race.comment: WILD WINNER (8) is racing well and is close to a win, the latest effort a solid second at Murray Bridge over 1800m. Looks well placed this line-up so expect another big run. LONGER ROUTE (7) improved last start but found one better over 1700m at this track. Finds a suitable race and can find the winner's circle. KIRKLISTON BLU (4) turned things around last start and landed the prize by a length as public elect over 2500m at Morphettville. Drops back in trip on the short turnaround but has found winning form and can keep the ball rolling. GRINZINGER BISHOP (3) chased soundly behind KIRKLISTON BLU last time but meets him better this time and can turn the tables. HARLEY'N'ROSE (12) comes through the same race and also meets them better. Don't dismiss.
